Description: Up for sale is a rare Epiphone John Lennon Limited Edition 1965 Revolution Casino in Natural color. The guitar comes with original hard case and all the paperwork. The guitar is in almost mint condition,as I inspect the whole guitar,I only see two small dings on the back of the headstock,other than that,the guitar is fine. All the parts are all 100% original,neck is straight,no fret wear,truss rod and electronics are in working condition. I will be listing lots of parts these few weeks as I'm running a shop that repairs guitars,amps,effect pedals etc.for over 30 years and I have lots of rare,vintage and interested parts in my shop to list. Sold as is,no returns No returns for items damaged in shipment. Kindly reminder: We will do our best to let buyer get more information of the item(s). Some items are used,the description is just our subjective judgment,maybe there is different opinion among individuals,so please check all the photos on my listing to judge yourself. Item sold as is,therefore wear and tear must be expected,please don't expect the items in perfect condition. If you have any question,please ask before you bid the item and I've will try our best to any all your questions and send more pictures of the item. The shipping cost for every item that we quoted on my listing is just the estimation, it is hard for us to state the exact shipping cost which is determined based on the distance between the area you live in and mine. I have to pay for material, labor, packaging as well as shipping costs. If you are not satisfied with the handling and shipping cost that we quoted on our listing, please do not bid the item and then request for a discount on the shipping cost. Bear in mind that sometimes we have to pay extra shipping cost to our buyer due to the over weight of the item. Once we have received payment,your item(s) will normally be dispatched within 3-5 working days.If you need your item immediately,please let us know and we will do our best to accommodate your request.
